                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <hr />
                <div class="modal-footer" style="margin-top: -20px;">
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-floppy-save"></i> Lưu lại</button>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" data-dismiss="modal"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-minus-sign"></i> Thoát</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <script> 
        document.getElementById("mainContentStory").value = "La Van Ha lives in one of the poorest provinces in Northern Viet Nam. Ha is 13, but has been working as a ragpicker at the landfill for four years now. He studied until class five, while working in the fields. He left school since the family didn’t have enough money to feed everybody. “Those were days that I cannot even think about. There was a lot of tension at home,” he says. The money he earns from picking rags has solved those problems to some extent, with his younger brother now being able to study at home, without working. “I told him, ‘Brother, you should study. Let me go but you should study.’ At least one person in the family should get educated, right?”, he says.  Ha future, however, remains bleak at best.";
